{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_9a2ef1c6905e4ad6bb684276","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<p align=\"center\">\n2\t  <img alt=\"giskardlogo\" src=\"readme/logo_light.png#gh-light-mode-only\">\n3\t  <img alt=\"giskardlogo\" src=\"readme/logo_dark.png#gh-dark-mode-only\">\n4\t</p>\n5\t<h1 align=\"center\" weight='300' >Evals, Red Teaming and Test Generation for Agentic Systems</h1>\n6\t<h3 align=\"center\" weight='300' >Modular, Lightweight, Dynamic and Async-first </h3>\n7\t<div align=\"center\">\n8\t\n9\t  [![GitHub release](https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/Giskard-AI/giskard)](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard/releases)\n10\t  [![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Apache_2.0-blue.svg)](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard/blob/main/LICENSE)\n11\t  [![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/giskard/month)](https://pepy.tech/project/giskard)\n12\t  [![CI](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard-oss/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg?branch=main)](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard-oss/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg?branch=main)\n13\t  [![Giskard on Discord](https://img.shields.io/discord/939190303397666868?label=Discord)](https://gisk.ar/discord)\n14\t\n15\t  <a rel=\"me\" href=\"https://fosstodon.org/@Giskard\"></a>\n16\t\n17\t</div>\n18\t<h3 align=\"center\">\n19\t   <a href=\"https://docs.giskard.ai/oss\"><b>Docs</b></a> &bull;\n20\t  <a href=\"https://www.giskard.ai/?utm_source=github&utm_medium=github&utm_campaign=github_readme&utm_id=readmeblog\"><b>Website</b></a> &bull;\n21\t  <a href=\"https://gisk.ar/discord\"><b>Community</b></a>\n22\t </h3>\n23\t<br />\n24\t\n25\t> [!IMPORTANT]\n26\t> **Giskard v3** is a fresh rewrite designed for dynamic, multi-turn testing of AI agents. This release drops heavy dependencies for better efficiency while introducing a more powerful AI vulnerability scanner and enhanced RAG evaluation capabilities. For now, the vulnerability scanner and RAG evaluation still rely on Giskard v2.\n27\t> **Giskard v2 remains available but is no longer actively maintained.**\n28\t> Follow progress → [Read the v3 Annoucement](https://github.com/orgs/Giskard-AI/discussions/2250) · [Roadmap](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard-oss/issues/2252)\n29\t\n30\t## Install\n31\t\n32\t```sh\n33\tpip install giskard\n34\t```\n35\t\n36\tRequires Python 3.12+.\n37\t\n38\t______________________________________________________________________\n39\t\n40\tGiskard is an open-source Python library for **testing and evaluating agentic systems**. The v3 architecture is a modular set of focused packages — each carrying only the dependencies it needs — built from scratch to wrap anything: an LLM, a black-box agent, or a multi-step pipeline.\n41\t\n42\t| Status | Package | Description |\n43\t|--------|---------|-------------|\n44\t| ✅ Alpha | `giskard-checks` | Testing & evaluation — scenario API, built-in checks, LLM-as-judge |\n45\t| 🚧 In progress | `giskard-scan` | Agent vulnerability scanner — red teaming, prompt injection, data leakage (successor of [v2 Scan](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai/en/stable/open_source/scan/index.html)) |\n46\t| 📋 Planned | `giskard-rag` | RAG evaluation & synthetic data generation (successor of [v2 RAGET](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai/en/stable/open_source/testset_generation/index.html)) |\n47\t\n48\t## Giskard Checks — create and apply evals for testing agents\n49\t\n50\t```sh\n51\tpip install giskard-checks\n52\t```\n53\t\n54\t**[Giskard Checks](https://docs.giskard.ai/oss/checks)** is a lightweight library for creating evaluations (evals) that test LLM-based systems — from simple assertions to LLM-as-judge assessments. Unlike traditional unit tests, evals are designed for **non-deterministic outputs** where the same input can produce different valid responses.\n55\t\n56\tUse Giskard Checks to:\n57\t- **Catch regressions** — verify your system still behaves correctly after changes\n58\t- **Validate RAG quality** — check if answers are grounded in retrieved context\n59\t- **Enforce safety rules** — ensure outputs conform to your content policies\n60\t- **Evaluate multi-turn agents** — test full conversations, not just single exchanges\n61\t\n62\tBuilt-in evals include string matching, comparisons, regex, semantic similarity, and LLM-as-judge checks (`Groundedness`, `Conformity`, `LLMJudge`).\n63\t\n64\t### Quickstart\n65\t\n66\t```python\n67\tfrom openai import OpenAI\n68\tfrom giskard.checks import Scenario, Groundedness\n69\t\n70\tclient = OpenAI()\n71\t\n72\tdef get_answer(inputs: str) -> str:\n73\t    response = client.chat.completions.create(\n74\t        model=\"gpt-5-mini\",\n75\t        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": inputs}],\n76\t    )\n77\t    return response.choices[0].message.content\n78\t\n79\tscenario = (\n80\t    Scenario(\"test_dynamic_output\")\n81\t    .interact(\n82\t        inputs=\"What is the capital of France?\",\n83\t        outputs=get_answer,\n84\t    )\n85\t    .check(\n86\t        Groundedness(\n87\t            name=\"answer is grounded\",\n88\t            answer_key=\"trace.last.outputs\",\n89\t            context=\"France is a country in Western Europe. Its capital is Paris.\",\n90\t        )\n91\t    )\n92\t)\n93\t\n94\tresult = await scenario.run()\n95\tresult.print_report()\n96\t```\n97\t\n98\t> The `run()` method is async. In a script, wrap it with `asyncio.run()`. See the [full docs](https://docs.giskard.ai/oss/checks) for `Suites`, `LLMJudge`, multi-turn scenarios, and more.\n99\t\n100\t\n101\t## Looking for Giskard v2?\n102\t\n103\tGiskard v2 included **Scan** (automatic vulnerability detection) and **RAGET** (RAG evaluation test set generation) for both ML models and LLM applications. These features are not available in v3.\n104\t\n105\t```sh\n106\tpip install \"giskard[llm]>2,<3\"\n107\t```\n108\t\n109\t### [Scan](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai/en/stable/open_source/scan/index.html) — automatically detect performance, bias & security issues\n110\t\n111\tWrap your model and run the scan:\n112\t\n113\t```python\n114\timport giskard\n115\timport pandas as pd\n116\t\n117\t# Replace my_llm_chain with your actual LLM chain or model inference logic\n118\tdef model_predict(df: pd.DataFrame):\n119\t    \"\"\"The function takes a DataFrame and must return a list of outputs (one per row).\"\"\"\n120\t    return [my_llm_chain.run({\"query\": question}) for question in df[\"question\"]]\n121\t\n122\tgiskard_model = giskard.Model(\n123\t    model=model_predict,\n124\t    model_type=\"text_generation\",\n125\t    name=\"My LLM Application\",\n126\t    description=\"A question answering assistant\",\n127\t    feature_names=[\"question\"],\n128\t)\n129\t\n130\tscan_results = giskard.scan(giskard_model)\n131\tdisplay(scan_results)\n132\t```\n133\t\n134\t<p align=\"center\">\n135\t  <img src=\"readme/scan_updated.gif\" alt=\"Scan Example\" width=\"800\">\n136\t</p>\n137\t\n138\t### [RAGET](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai/en/stable/open_source/testset_generation/index.html) — generate evaluation datasets for RAG applications\n139\t\n140\tAutomatically generate questions, reference answers, and context from your knowledge base:\n141\t\n142\t```python\n143\timport pandas as pd\n144\tfrom giskard.rag import generate_testset, KnowledgeBase\n145\t\n146\t# Load your knowledge base documents\n147\tdf = pd.read_csv(\"path/to/your/knowledge_base.csv\")\n148\tknowledge_base = KnowledgeBase.from_pandas(df, columns=[\"column_1\", \"column_2\"])\n149\t\n150\ttestset = generate_testset(\n151\t    knowledge_base,\n152\t    num_questions=60,\n153\t    language='en',\n154\t    agent_description=\"A customer support chatbot for company X\",\n155\t)\n156\t```\n157\t\n158\t<p align=\"center\">\n159\t  <img src=\"readme/RAGET_updated.gif\" alt=\"RAGET Example\" width=\"800\">\n160\t</p>\n161\t\n162\t[Full v2 docs](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai)\n163\t\n164\t<h1 id=\"community\">👋 Community</h1>\n165\t\n166\tWe welcome contributions from the AI community! Read this [guide](./CONTRIBUTING.md) to get started, and join our thriving community on [Discord](https://gisk.ar/discord).\n167\t\n168\tFollow the progress and share feedback:\n169\t[v3 Announcement](https://github.com/orgs/Giskard-AI/discussions/2250) · [Roadmap](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard-oss/issues/2252)\n170\t\n171\t🌟 [Leave us a star](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard), it helps the project to get discovered by others and keeps us motivated to build awesome open-source tools! 🌟\n172\t\n173\t❤️ If you find our work useful, please consider [sponsoring us](https://github.com/sponsors/Giskard-AI) on GitHub. With a monthly sponsoring, you can get a sponsor badge, display your company in this readme, and get your bug reports prioritized. We also offer one-time sponsoring if you want us to get involved in a consulting project, run a workshop, or give a talk at your company.\n174\t\n175\t<h2 id=\"sponsors\">💚 Current sponsors</h2>\n176\t\n177\tWe thank the following companies which are sponsoring our project with monthly donations:\n178\t\n179\t**[Lunary](https://lunary.ai/)**\n180\t\n181\t<img src=\"https://lunary.ai/logo-blue-bg.svg\" alt=\"Lunary logo\" width=\"100\"/>\n182\t\n183\t**[Biolevate](https://www.biolevate.com/)**\n184\t\n185\t<img src=\"https://awsmp-logos.s3.amazonaws.com/seller-wgamx5z6umune/2d10badd2ccac49699096ea7fb986b98.png\" alt=\"Biolevate logo\" width=\"400\"/>\n186\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cecb49f1-a503-4314-99a9-a51144ba81d8","uuid":"ff78a9e0-53e6-456b-b976-7e61edc636f3","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:30:21.866Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"<p align=\"center\">\n  <img alt=\"giskardlogo\" src=\"readme/logo_light.png#gh-light-mode-only\">\n  <img alt=\"giskardlogo\" src=\"readme/logo_dark.png#gh-dark-mode-only\">\n</p>\n<h1 align=\"center\" weight='300' >Evals, Red Teaming and Test Generation for Agentic Systems</h1>\n<h3 align=\"center\" weight='300' >Modular, Lightweight, Dynamic and Async-first </h3>\n<div align=\"center\">\n\n  [![GitHub release](https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/Giskard-AI/giskard)](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard/releases)\n  [![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Apache_2.0-blue.svg)](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard/blob/main/LICENSE)\n  [![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/giskard/month)](https://pepy.tech/project/giskard)\n  [![CI](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard-oss/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg?branch=main)](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard-oss/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg?branch=main)\n  [![Giskard on Discord](https://img.shields.io/discord/939190303397666868?label=Discord)](https://gisk.ar/discord)\n\n  <a rel=\"me\" href=\"https://fosstodon.org/@Giskard\"></a>\n\n</div>\n<h3 align=\"center\">\n   <a href=\"https://docs.giskard.ai/oss\"><b>Docs</b></a> &bull;\n  <a href=\"https://www.giskard.ai/?utm_source=github&utm_medium=github&utm_campaign=github_readme&utm_id=readmeblog\"><b>Website</b></a> &bull;\n  <a href=\"https://gisk.ar/discord\"><b>Community</b></a>\n </h3>\n<br />\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> **Giskard v3** is a fresh rewrite designed for dynamic, multi-turn testing of AI agents. This release drops heavy dependencies for better efficiency while introducing a more powerful AI vulnerability scanner and enhanced RAG evaluation capabilities. For now, the vulnerability scanner and RAG evaluation still rely on Giskard v2.\n> **Giskard v2 remains available but is no longer actively maintained.**\n> Follow progress → [Read the v3 Annoucement](https://github.com/orgs/Giskard-AI/discussions/2250) · [Roadmap](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard-oss/issues/2252)\n\n## Install\n\n```sh\npip install giskard\n```\n\nRequires Python 3.12+.\n\n______________________________________________________________________\n\nGiskard is an open-source Python library for **testing and evaluating agentic systems**. The v3 architecture is a modular set of focused packages — each carrying only the dependencies it needs — built from scratch to wrap anything: an LLM, a black-box agent, or a multi-step pipeline.\n\n| Status | Package | Description |\n|--------|---------|-------------|\n| ✅ Alpha | `giskard-checks` | Testing & evaluation — scenario API, built-in checks, LLM-as-judge |\n| 🚧 In progress | `giskard-scan` | Agent vulnerability scanner — red teaming, prompt injection, data leakage (successor of [v2 Scan](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai/en/stable/open_source/scan/index.html)) |\n| 📋 Planned | `giskard-rag` | RAG evaluation & synthetic data generation (successor of [v2 RAGET](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai/en/stable/open_source/testset_generation/index.html)) |\n\n## Giskard Checks — create and apply evals for testing agents\n\n```sh\npip install giskard-checks\n```\n\n**[Giskard Checks](https://docs.giskard.ai/oss/checks)** is a lightweight library for creating evaluations (evals) that test LLM-based systems — from simple assertions to LLM-as-judge assessments. Unlike traditional unit tests, evals are designed for **non-deterministic outputs** where the same input can produce different valid responses.\n\nUse Giskard Checks to:\n- **Catch regressions** — verify your system still behaves correctly after changes\n- **Validate RAG quality** — check if answers are grounded in retrieved context\n- **Enforce safety rules** — ensure outputs conform to your content policies\n- **Evaluate multi-turn agents** — test full conversations, not just single exchanges\n\nBuilt-in evals include string matching, comparisons, regex, semantic similarity, and LLM-as-judge checks (`Groundedness`, `Conformity`, `LLMJudge`).\n\n### Quickstart\n\n```python\nfrom openai import OpenAI\nfrom giskard.checks import Scenario, Groundedness\n\nclient = OpenAI()\n\ndef get_answer(inputs: str) -> str:\n    response = client.chat.completions.create(\n        model=\"gpt-5-mini\",\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": inputs}],\n    )\n    return response.choices[0].message.content\n\nscenario = (\n    Scenario(\"test_dynamic_output\")\n    .interact(\n        inputs=\"What is the capital of France?\",\n        outputs=get_answer,\n    )\n    .check(\n        Groundedness(\n            name=\"answer is grounded\",\n            answer_key=\"trace.last.outputs\",\n            context=\"France is a country in Western Europe. Its capital is Paris.\",\n        )\n    )\n)\n\nresult = await scenario.run()\nresult.print_report()\n```\n\n> The `run()` method is async. In a script, wrap it with `asyncio.run()`. See the [full docs](https://docs.giskard.ai/oss/checks) for `Suites`, `LLMJudge`, multi-turn scenarios, and more.\n\n\n## Looking for Giskard v2?\n\nGiskard v2 included **Scan** (automatic vulnerability detection) and **RAGET** (RAG evaluation test set generation) for both ML models and LLM applications. These features are not available in v3.\n\n```sh\npip install \"giskard[llm]>2,<3\"\n```\n\n### [Scan](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai/en/stable/open_source/scan/index.html) — automatically detect performance, bias & security issues\n\nWrap your model and run the scan:\n\n```python\nimport giskard\nimport pandas as pd\n\n# Replace my_llm_chain with your actual LLM chain or model inference logic\ndef model_predict(df: pd.DataFrame):\n    \"\"\"The function takes a DataFrame and must return a list of outputs (one per row).\"\"\"\n    return [my_llm_chain.run({\"query\": question}) for question in df[\"question\"]]\n\ngiskard_model = giskard.Model(\n    model=model_predict,\n    model_type=\"text_generation\",\n    name=\"My LLM Application\",\n    description=\"A question answering assistant\",\n    feature_names=[\"question\"],\n)\n\nscan_results = giskard.scan(giskard_model)\ndisplay(scan_results)\n```\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"readme/scan_updated.gif\" alt=\"Scan Example\" width=\"800\">\n</p>\n\n### [RAGET](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai/en/stable/open_source/testset_generation/index.html) — generate evaluation datasets for RAG applications\n\nAutomatically generate questions, reference answers, and context from your knowledge base:\n\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom giskard.rag import generate_testset, KnowledgeBase\n\n# Load your knowledge base documents\ndf = pd.read_csv(\"path/to/your/knowledge_base.csv\")\nknowledge_base = KnowledgeBase.from_pandas(df, columns=[\"column_1\", \"column_2\"])\n\ntestset = generate_testset(\n    knowledge_base,\n    num_questions=60,\n    language='en',\n    agent_description=\"A customer support chatbot for company X\",\n)\n```\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"readme/RAGET_updated.gif\" alt=\"RAGET Example\" width=\"800\">\n</p>\n\n[Full v2 docs](https://legacy-docs.giskard.ai)\n\n<h1 id=\"community\">👋 Community</h1>\n\nWe welcome contributions from the AI community! Read this [guide](./CONTRIBUTING.md) to get started, and join our thriving community on [Discord](https://gisk.ar/discord).\n\nFollow the progress and share feedback:\n[v3 Announcement](https://github.com/orgs/Giskard-AI/discussions/2250) · [Roadmap](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard-oss/issues/2252)\n\n🌟 [Leave us a star](https://github.com/Giskard-AI/giskard), it helps the project to get discovered by others and keeps us motivated to build awesome open-source tools! 🌟\n\n❤️ If you find our work useful, please consider [sponsoring us](https://github.com/sponsors/Giskard-AI) on GitHub. With a monthly sponsoring, you can get a sponsor badge, display your company in this readme, and get your bug reports prioritized. We also offer one-time sponsoring if you want us to get involved in a consulting project, run a workshop, or give a talk at your company.\n\n<h2 id=\"sponsors\">💚 Current sponsors</h2>\n\nWe thank the following companies which are sponsoring our project with monthly donations:\n\n**[Lunary](https://lunary.ai/)**\n\n<img src=\"https://lunary.ai/logo-blue-bg.svg\" alt=\"Lunary logo\" width=\"100\"/>\n\n**[Biolevate](https://www.biolevate.com/)**\n\n<img src=\"https://awsmp-logos.s3.amazonaws.com/seller-wgamx5z6umune/2d10badd2ccac49699096ea7fb986b98.png\" alt=\"Biolevate logo\" width=\"400\"/>\n","numLines":186,"startLine":1,"totalLines":186}}}
